        decision: 'Designed five distinct visual languages that never share shapes or color logic. Event severity uses tally bars in colored pills. Work order urgency uses circle fill hierarchy (filled, hollow, clock) in neutral gray. Investigation status uses right-pointing triangles (filled for active, hollow for waiting). Asset criticality uses letter-grade pills (A Safety, B Production, C Support). Asset status uses small colored dots with text labels. Each system is readable without color alone (WCAG SC 1.4.1).',
        why: 'An enterprise dashboard has multiple classification systems competing for attention on the same screen. If two systems look the same, the engineer has to read the label to tell them apart. Distinct shape families let them pattern-match at a glance: "pill with bars means event, circle means work order, triangle means investigation." The visual separation also means each system can evolve independently without creating new collisions.',
