        decision: 'Price labels explain what the number means, not just what it is. Sale type badges use color to signal risk: green for liens cleared, amber for liens survive. A tooltip on every price explains in plain language what the buyer is actually paying. The "Before you bid" checklist changes per sale type so buyers know exactly what due diligence to do.',
